
[1]purslain

   PURS'LAIN, n. [The Latin is portulaca. See Leek.]

   A plant of the genus Portulaca. The sea purslain is of the genus
   Atriplex. The tree sea purslain is the Atriplex halimus. (See Purslain
   tree.) The water purslain is of the genus Peplis.
